tp:docstring.p:
Mapping representing a class of channels that can be requested
          from a connection manager, can be handled by a user interface,
          are supported by a contact, etc.

ul.li:
class 2: Channel.ChannelType = Text,
              Channel.TargetHandleType = CONTACT,
              Encryption.Encrypted = TRUE

alt - d: altitude in metres above sea level (negative
              if below sea level)

                This is from XEP-0080

tp:docstring.p:
The type of relay server that this represents depends on
          the value of the NATTraversal
          property. If NATTraversal is ice-udp, this is a TURN server;
          if NATTraversal is gtalk-p2p, this is a Google relay server;
          otherwise, the meaning of RelayInfo is undefined.

signal.tp:deprecated:
There is no case where you want to release candidates (except
for an ICE reset, and there you'd want to replace then all,
using SetRemoteCandidateList).
